      • copyChunkTree

        public org.antlr.runtime.tree.CommonTree copyChunkTree(org.antlr.runtime.tree.CommonTree chunk)
        creates a symbolic copy (i.e., no parameters) of the specified chunk. To correctly add it to the model AST, the returned tree must:
        1) have its name changed to a unique identifier
        2) be added as a child of the chunktype AST's CHUNKS subtree.
        If this is to be inserted into a buffer, it must also be added to that buffer's CHUNKS subtree.
        Parameters:
        chunk -
        Returns:
